-3
      " id=3D"section-how-to-interpret-quartiles">How To Interpret Quartile=
s?
</h2><p class=3D"text-grey col-span-10 md:col-span-8 lg:col-span-6 md:col-s=
tart-2 lg:col-start-3">Quartiles are =E2=80=8Clisted as a set of numbers or=
 shown visually using a box plot or a box and whisker plot.=20

</p><p class=3D"text-grey col-span-10 md:col-span-8 lg:col-span-6 md:col-st=
art-2 lg:col-start-3">A <a href=3D"https://articles.outlier.org/how-to-make=
-a-box-plot" class=3D"text-green hover:underline focus:underline">box plot =
</a>is a graph in the shape of a rectangle. The two shorter sides of the re=
ctangle mark the lower and upper quartiles, and a line in the middle of the=
 rectangle marks the median (Q2).=20

</p><p class=3D"text-grey col-span-10 md:col-span-8 lg:col-span-6 md:col-st=
art-2 lg:col-start-3">A box plot with two lines stretching out from either =
end of the rectangle is called a box and whisker plot. In addition to the t=
hree quartiles, a box and whisker plot marks the minimum and the maximum of=
 your data.



</p><div class=3D"col-span-10 md:col-span-8 md:col-start-2 md:grid grid-col=
s-8 md:gap-x-[24px] lg:gap-x-[36px]"><div class=3D"col-span-8 flex justify-=
